<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-06-03T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-06-03T16:00:00-05:00" n="388" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d388">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">893.50 Recovery/6–349: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                            to the Consul at Taipei</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Edgar</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-06-03T17:00:00-04:00">June 3, 1949—5
                                p. m.</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>118. Dept is reopening in NSC question substantial ECA assistance to Taiwan.
                        Decision expected within 2 weeks. For ur conf info and discreet transmission
                        Craig and Griffin respectively activation industrial reconstruction program
                        or other massive economic aid appears improbable.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Webb</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>